# Internet Checksum (Binary Input) Simulator

A Python -based simulator for computing and verifying checksums in binary data transmission. This project is designed to help understand how checksums are used to ensure data integrity during transmission.

## Project Overview

This project simulates the process of transmitting binary data and uses checksums to detect errors that may occur during transmission. It includes functionalities to:
- Convert binary strings to byte vectors.
- Compute checksums.
- Simulate errors in data transmission.
- Verify data integrity using checksums.

## Submitted To

